The University of Essex has a clear financial framework in place to help mitigate the risk of financial insolvency, which includes: 
1. Achieving an annual minimum cash surplus of 5.5%; 
2. Ensuring earnings before interest, tax, depreciation, and amortisation are at least 2 times annual debt servicing costs; 
3. Maintaining minimum liquid funds equal to 60 days of expenditure; 
4. Requiring all Departments/Schools to generate a cash surplus or have a recovery plan to return to break-even within 3 years; 
5. Only funding projects from external borrowing where servicing costs can be met from additional income or savings.

Sources: https://www.essex.ac.uk/-/media/documents/about/governance/ofs/student-protection-plan.pdf
